# [QIRG](../wg/qirg.html)

## Summary
The Quantum Internet Research Group (QIRG) met at IETF 126. The session featured progress updates on three active drafts, an introduction to a synthetic emulation environment, a discussion of near-term applications of quantum networks beyond Quantum Key Distribution (QKD), an overview of European standardization efforts (EuroQCI), and an update on the Quantum Datagram Control Protocol (QDCP). 

---

## Key Discussion Points

### 1. Welcome and Group Administration
*Wojtek Kozlowski* opened the session, reminding participants of the standard IETF and IRTF codes of conduct and noting that the IRTF focuses on research collaboration rather than standardization. 
* **Slide Deck**: [Chair Slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-qirg-chair-slides-00)
* **Group Status**: The research group currently has two published documents, one adopted draft, and six active individual drafts.

