### 6. EuroQCI Standardization
*Christoph Spryxis* provided an overview of the European Quantum Communication Infrastructure (EuroQCI) and its standardization efforts.
* **Slide Deck**: [EuroQCI Standardisation](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-qirg-euroqci-standardisation-01)
* **Details**:
  * EuroQCI is an EU-wide initiative across 27 member states, partnering with the European Space Agency (ESA) to deploy secure quantum infrastructure using terrestrial and satellite links.
  * The initiative relies on CEF (Connecting Europe Facility) funding to establish cross-border fiber and satellite optical ground stations (OGS).
  * A new 36-month coordination and support project, "Harmonic QCI", has been awarded to coordinate standardization. Its pillars include telecommunication network integration (space/terrestrial), security integration (hybridizing QKD with PQC), and QKD component/system standardization.
* **Discussion**:
  * *Wojtek Kozlowski* asked which Standard Development Organizations (SDOs) are the focus. *Christoph Spryxis* identified ETSI and CEN/CENELEC JTC 22 WG4 as primary targets.
  * *Ben Roberts* asked how the network plans to reach long-distance overseas territories. *Christoph Spryxis* noted that satellite-based communication is the designated solution for spanning these extreme distances.
  * *Rodney Van Meter* noted a formatting issue in the uploaded slides on the data tracker and shared that IEEE Quantum Week (mid-September in Toronto) would feature a day-long workshop on international standards.

